.TH "STARTFLUXBOX-WAYLAND" "1" "18 January 2026" "startfluxbox-wayland" "Fluxbox Manual"
.nh
.ad l
.SH "NAME"
startfluxbox-wayland \- start a fluxbox-wayland session
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.sp
\fBstartfluxbox-wayland\fR [\-h] [\-c \fISTARTUPFILE\fR]
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.sp
\fBstartfluxbox-wayland(1)\fR is a helper script for starting \fBfluxbox-wayland(1)\fR from a tty, SSH shell, or display manager.
It runs a startup script (by default \fB~/\&.fluxbox/startup-wayland\fR); if it does not exist, it is generated.
.sp
The script also sets Wayland-oriented session environment variables and ensures a usable \fBXDG_RUNTIME_DIR\fR.
If no DBus session is available and \fBdbus-run-session\fR exists, it runs the startup script under a private DBus session.
.SH "OPTIONS"
.PP
\fB\-c\fR, \fB\-\-config\fR \fISTARTUPFILE\fR
.RS 4
Use an alternate startup script instead of \fB~/\&.fluxbox/startup-wayland\fR.
.RE
.PP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
.RS 4
Display a short usage message.
.RE
.SH "FILES"
.PP
\fB~/\&.fluxbox/startup-wayland\fR
.RS 4
Startup script executed before launching \fBfluxbox-wayland(1)\fR. Lines starting with \fB#\fR are treated as comments.
.RE
.SH "ENVIRONMENT"
.sp
\fBstartfluxbox-wayland(1)\fR sets (if not already set) the following variables:
.PP
\fBXDG_SESSION_TYPE\fR
.RS 4
Set to \fBwayland\fR.
.RE
.PP
\fBXDG_CURRENT_DESKTOP\fR
.RS 4
Defaults to \fBFluxbox\fR.
.RE
.PP
\fBXDG_SESSION_DESKTOP\fR, \fBDESKTOP_SESSION\fR
.RS 4
Defaults to \fBfluxbox-wayland\fR.
.RE
.PP
\fBXDG_RUNTIME_DIR\fR
.RS 4
If unset, defaults to \fB/tmp/xdg-runtime-$UID\fR and is created with mode 0700. Wayland sockets live here.
.RE
.SH "EXAMPLES"
.sp
The generated \fB~/\&.fluxbox/startup-wayland\fR looks like this:
.sp
.if n \{\
.RS 4
.\}
.nf
#!/bin/sh
#
# fluxbox-wayland startup-script:
#
# Lines starting with a '#' are ignored.

# Applications you want to run with fluxbox-wayland.
# MAKE SURE THAT APPS THAT KEEP RUNNING HAVE AN '&' AT THE END.
#
# waybar &
# xdg-desktop-portal-wlr &

# And last but not least we start fluxbox-wayland.
exec fluxbox-wayland
.fi
.if n \{\
.RE
.\}
